  "summary": "Alexander Bonaparte Cast sits at breakfast appearing unwell and anxious. His landlady, Mrs. Marbury, expresses concern over his lack of appetite, but Cast insists he must travel to Cheltenham for an important appointment to protect his professional reputation. During their conversation, Mrs. Marbury mentions that the ABC killer is predicted to strike in Tadcaster tomorrow during a horse race, a topic that causes Cast visible tension. After she leaves, Cast packs his luggage, including several flat cardboard boxes, and prepares to depart.\n\nIn the hallway, Cast speaks with Miss Lily, a girl from an adjoining room, asking if she believes in omens or premonitions before saying a heavy goodbye. Lily notes that Cast had been near the site of the previous ABC murder in Torquay and remarks that he seems \"crazy\" after his departure.\n\nMeanwhile, following a suggestion from Hercule Poirot, Inspector Croome instructs his subordinates to obtain lists of all stocking manufacturers and agents, despite some skepticism regarding Poirot's abilities.\n\nLater, Tom Hattinger informs Lily that he saw Mr. Cast at Euston station. Tom claims he found Cast's lost ticket and asserts that Cast is actually traveling to Doncaster for a horse race rather than Cheltenham. Lily becomes concerned because the next predicted location for the ABC murders is Doncaster. She recalls that during the previous murder in Bexhill, Cast had gone to the beach because he had forgotten his swimming trunks. While Tom jokingly suggests that Cast might be the killer, Lily dismisses the idea.",
